          "block_order": 1
        },
        {
          "block_label": "paragraph_title",
          "block_content": "1.27True or false, with reason if true and counterexampeif false:",
          "block_bbox": [
            320,
            468,
            2431,
            549
          ],
          "block_id": 3,
          "block_order": 2
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(1) If $L_{1}U_{1}=L_{2}U_{2}$ (upper triangular $U^{\\prime}s$ with nonzero diagonal, lower triangular $L^{\\prime}\\mathrm{s}$ with unit diagonal), then $L_{1}=L_{2}\\ and\\ U_{1}=U_{2}$ . The LU factorization is unique.\n",
          "block_bbox": [
            502,
            624,
            3098,
            902
          ],
          "block_id": 4,
          "block_order": 3
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(2)$\\operatorname{I f}A^{2}+A=I\\operatorname{t h e n}A^{-1}=A+I.$ ",
          "block_bbox": [
            504,
            937,
            1619,
            1016
          ],
          "block_id": 5,
          "block_order": 4
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(3) If all diagonal entries of A are zero, then A is singular.",
          "block_bbox": [
            501,
            1063,
            2324,
            1139
          ],
          "block_id": 6,
          "block_order": 5
        },
        {
          "block_label": "paragraph_title",
          "block_content": "1.28 By experiment or the Gauss-Jordan method compute ",
          "block_bbox": [
            316,
            1207,
            2169,
            1284
          ],
          "block_id": 7,
          "block_order": 6
        },
        {
          "block_label": "formula",
          "block_content": "\\begin{array}{r l r l r}{\\left[\\begin{matrix}{1}&{0}&{0}\\\\ {\\ell}&{1}&{0}\\\\ {m}&{0}&{1}\\end{matrix}\\right]^{n},}&{{}}&{\\left[\\begin{matrix}{1}&{0}&{0}\\\\ {\\ell}&{1}&{0}\\\\ {m}&{0}&{1}\\end{matrix}\\right]^{-1},}&{{}}&{\\left[\\begin{matrix}{1}&{0}&{0}\\\\ {\\ell}&{1}&{0}\\\\ {0}&{m}&{1}\\end{matrix}\\right]^{-1}.}\\end{array}",
          "block_bbox": [
            964,
            1345,
            2664,
            1701
          ],
          "block_id": 8,
          "block_order": 7
        },
        {
          "block_label": "paragraph_title",
          "block_content": "1.29 Write down the 2 by 2 matrices that ",
          "block_bbox": [
            294,
            1777,
            1634,
            1851
          ],
          "block_id": 9,
          "block_order": 8
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(a) reverse the direction of every vector.",
          "block_bbox": [
            477,
            1933,
            1778,
            2003
          ],
          "block_id": 10,
          "block_order": 9
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(b) project every vector onto the $x_{2}$ axis.",
          "block_bbox": [
            470,
            2059,
            1787,
            2133
          ],
          "block_id": 11,
          "block_order": 10
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(c) turn every vector counterclockwise through 90°.",
